CHAPTER ______
1 AN ACT concerning
2 State Procurement – Competitive Proof of Concept Procurement
3 FOR the purpose of establishing competitive proof of concept procurements as an
4 authorized procurement method; providing that a competitive proof of concept
5 procurement may have multiple phases of evaluation; requiring a unit of State
6 government to obtain the approval of the Chief Procurement Officer or a designee
7 before conducting a certain competitive proof of concept procurement; requiring a
8 unit of State government to obtain the approval of the Secretary of Information
9 Technology or a designee before conducting a certain competitive proof of concept
10 procurement for information technology; repealing a provision that authorizes a
11 competitive proof of concept procurement to be conducted through certain
12 procurement methods; altering the required contents of a competitive proof of
13 concept solicitation; requiring competitive proof of concept solicitations to be posted
14 on eMaryland Marketplace Advantage; altering procedures for conducting a
